The solution is to move the configuration of the Maven plugin `quarkus-maven-plugin` to the section `pluginManagement`of the parent&#39;s `pom.xml`.

    &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;pluginManagement&gt;
            &lt;plugins&gt;
                &lt;plugin&gt;
                    &lt;groupId&gt;${quarkus.platform.group-id}&lt;/groupId&gt;
                    &lt;artifactId&gt;quarkus-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                    &lt;version&gt;${quarkus.platform.version}&lt;/version&gt;
                    &lt;executions&gt;
                        &lt;execution&gt;
                            &lt;goals&gt;
                                &lt;goal&gt;build&lt;/goal&gt;
                            &lt;/goals&gt;
                        &lt;/execution&gt;
                    &lt;/executions&gt;
                &lt;/plugin&gt;
            &lt;/plugins&gt;
        &lt;/pluginManagement&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;

Afterwards, add just the plugin to the module, in this case the module which contains the endpoints (resource class).

    &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;${quarkus.platform.group-id}&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;quarkus-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;

This way, it&#39;ll be possible to run `quarkus dev` goal from the main folder of the project.

